Purpose

This webpage/report is intended to aggregate information from different agencies (i.e.USACE, SFWMD, FWC, USGS and NOAA) into one spot to help inform local government agencies and stakeholders on conditions within Lake Okeechobee, the Caloosahatchee River and Estuary and Coastal southwest Florida. The data provided here should be considered preliminary and are subject to change.

Caloosahatchee Conditions Summary: Flow to the Caloosahatchee Estuary had a 7-day average of 2,581 cfs at S-79 with a 7-day average of 331 cfs (13%) coming from the lake at S-77. The 14-day moving average flow at S-79 is 2,752 cfs and has been in the damaging flow envelope (> 2600 cfs; RECOVER 2020) for 30 days.

Lake Flows: In the past 7 days the total outflow from Lake Okeechobee was 7,413 AF with 4,594 AF to the Caloosahatchee through S-77,2,680 AF through S-308 in Port Mayaca, 122 AF through S-310 in Clewiston, and 0 AF to the EAA through S-351, S-352, and S-354. The total net inflow to the Lake was 45,619 AF (45,453 AF from Fisheating Creek, S-71, S-72, S-84s, S-65EX, and S-65EX1) with a total backflow volume of 166 AF from S310 and C10A. Water conservation areas received flows of 8,055 AF, 16,556 AF, and 19,773 AF at WCA1, WCA2, and WCA3, respectively. Everglades National Park received 25,438 AF.

Relative Algae Condition

Sonde monitoring locations within Lake Okeechobee conducted by SFWMD.


Daily Chlorophyll, Phycocyanin,relative ratio of Phycocyanin (Phyco) relative to Phyco and Chlorophyll (Chl) and Turbidity within Lake Okeechobee monitored by SFWMD. Chlorophyll and Phycocyanin are plotted on log-scale. Thresholds of concern/risk identified for Chlorophyll (20 and 40 g/L) and Phycocyanin (40 g/L; Cotterill et al 2019 & Macrio et al 2015).

Data are provisional and subject to change.

  • Cotterill et al (2019) Phycocyanin sensors as an early warning system for cyanobacteria blooms concentrations: a case study in the Rotorua lakes. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research 53:555570.
  • Macrio et al (2015) New insights towards the establishment of phycocyanin concentration thresholds considering species-specific variability of bloom-forming cyanobacteria. Hydrobiologia 757:155165.

Blue-Green Algae Sampling Results
